<recipe>
    <name>Chicken with Cashew Nuts (KAI PHAT MET MUANG HIMAPHAAN)</name>
    <indexCharacter>c</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>4</servings>
    <instructions>TAKE the stems off the dried chillies, cut each child into 1/2 inch pieces with scissors or a sharp knife and discard the seeds. MIX the fish sauce, oyster sauce and sugar in a small bowl. 

HEAT the oil in a wok over a medium heat and stir-fry the cashew nuts for 2 to 3 minutes or until light brown. Remove with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels. 

STIR-FRY the chillies in the same oil over a medium heat for 1 minute. They should darken but not blacken and burn. Remove from the pan with a slotted spoon. 

HEAT the same oil again and stir-fry half the garlic over a medium heat until light brown. Add half the chicken and stir-fry over a high heat for 4 to 5 minutes or until the chicken is cooked. Remove from the wok and repeat with the remaining garlic and chicken. Return all the chicken to the wok. 

ADD the red bell pepper, carrot, onion and the sauce mixture to the wok and stir-fry for 1 to 2 minutes. Taste, then adjust the seasoning if necessary. 

ADD the cashew nuts, chillies and spring onions and toss well. Sprinkle with ground pepper.</instructions>
